Philippine Stocks: Banco de Oro, Lepanto, Philex Mining

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-05-03T04:30:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/philippine-stocks-banco-de-oro-lepanto-philex-mining.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.2 percent to
4,319.37.  Metals producers:  Lepanto Consolidated Mining (LC)  Co.’s Class A
shares (LC PM), which are reserved for Filipinos, decreased 2.9
percent to 67 centavos, the sharpest percentage loss in the
benchmark  stock index .  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , the nation’s
largest metals producer, fell 2.3 percent to 18 pesos.  Gold for immediate delivery declined as much as 2.1 percent
while the price of copper for delivery in three months decreased
as much as 1.1 percent.  Banco de Oro Unibank Inc. (BDO)  , the nation’s biggest
bank by assets, increased 2.9 percent to 56.10 pesos, the
sharpest advance since Dec. 2. The lender said it entered into
an agreement with SM Keppel Land Inc. for the development and
expansion of a shopping mall complex.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in  Manila  at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  